<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="493" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,325,604]" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,434,460]" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bispo &amp; Novaes" authorityYear="2014" box="[325,553,434,460]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="corae">
<emphasis box="[325,553,434,460]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">Anacroneuria corae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected at the Serra dos Pireneus, 
<collectingRegion box="[1029,1159,434,460]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">Goiás state</collectingRegion>
. This species was originally described in the Cidade de 
<collectingRegion box="[532,600,470,496]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">Goiás</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[614,740,470,496]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">Goiás state</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bispo, P. C. &amp; Costa, L. S. M. &amp; Novaes, M. C." box="[757,962,470,496]" pageId="6" pageNumber="493" pagination="591 - 596" refId="ref8412" refString="Bispo, P. C., Costa, L. S. M. &amp; Novaes, M. C. (2014) Two new species and a new record of Anacroneuria (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from Central Brazil. Zootaxa, 3779 (5), 591 - 596. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3779.5.9" type="journal article" year="2014">
Bispo 
<emphasis box="[834,885,470,496]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">et al</emphasis>
. 2014
</bibRefCitation>
). Recently, the geographic distribution of the species was expanded to 
<collectingRegion box="[474,641,506,532]" country="Brazil" name="Tocantins" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">Tocantins state</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rippel, M. L. S. &amp; Novaes, M. C. &amp; Krolow, T. K." box="[656,864,506,532]" pageId="6" pageNumber="493" pagination="355 - 364" refId="ref10392" refString="Rippel, M. L. S., Novaes, M. C. &amp; Krolow, T. K. (2019) First records of genus Anacroneuria (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from Tocantins State, Brazil and description of a new species. Zootaxa, 4560 (2), 355 - 364. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4560.2.8" type="journal article" year="2019">
Rippel 
<emphasis box="[740,789,506,532]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
). The specimens collected agree with the 
<typeStatus box="[1331,1433,506,532]" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">holotype</typeStatus>
. However, one of the specimens studied did not show wing with a distal less pigmented circular area (
<figureCitation box="[1295,1424,542,568]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1528,1552]" captionTargetBox="[167,1383,365,1487]" captionTargetId="figure-102@3.[151,1435,344,1504]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male adult of Anacroneuria amargosa (A–C) and Anacroneuria corae (D–F). A, D: head and pronotum; B, E: anterior wing; C, F: posterior wing. Scale 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816761" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816761/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">Figs. 2E–F</figureCitation>
), characteristic of the species (
<bibRefCitation author="Bispo, P. C. &amp; Costa, L. S. M. &amp; Novaes, M. C." box="[475,672,578,604]" pageId="6" pageNumber="493" pagination="591 - 596" refId="ref8412" refString="Bispo, P. C., Costa, L. S. M. &amp; Novaes, M. C. (2014) Two new species and a new record of Anacroneuria (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from Central Brazil. Zootaxa, 3779 (5), 591 - 596. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3779.5.9" type="journal article" year="2014">
Bispo 
<emphasis box="[548,598,578,604]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">et al</emphasis>
. 2014
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
